t produc-\ntion in silicon determined by density functional theory molecular dynamics\nsimulations,” Phys. Rev. B 78, 045202 (2008).\n19S. Goedecker, T. Deutsch, and L. Billard, “A fourfold coordinated poi', 'utsch, and L. Billard, “A fourfold coordinated point\ndefect in silicon,” Phys. Rev. Lett. 88, 235501 (2002).\n20G. Angloher, S. Banik, G. Benato, et al., “Latest observations on the low\nenergy excess in CRESST-III,” SciPost Phys. Proc. , 013 (2023).\n21T. Sato and K. Niita, “Analytical functions to predict cosmic-ray neutron\nspectra in the atmosphere,” Radiation Research 166, 544–555 (2006).\n22T. Sato, H. Yasuda, K. Niita, A. Endo, and L. Sihver, “Development of\nparma: Phits-based analytical radiation model i', 'of\nparma: Phits-based analytical radiation model in the atmosphere,” Radia-\ntion Research 170, 244–259 (2008).\n23T. Sato, “Analytical model for estimating terrestrial cosmic ray fluxes nearly\nanytime and anywhere in the world: Extension of PARMA/EXPACS,”\nPLOS ONE 10, e0144679 (2015).\n24T. Sato, “Analytical model for estimating the zenith angle dependence of\nterrestrial cosmic ray fluxes,” PLOS ONE 11, e0160390 (2016).\n25J. Lindhard and M. Scharff, “Energy dissipation by ions in the keV region,”\nPhysical Rev'], 'model': 'qwen3-embedding-0.6b', 'encoding_format': 'base64'}}
